# Platform runtime artifacts — regenerate via nexus_platform.brain_builder
data/platform.db
# NOTE: the demo-company brains (data/demo_companies/*/brain/) are intentionally
# COMMITTED, not ignored. They are built once locally and pushed so CI can run the
# RAG-boundary tests against a real index without rebuilding on every run. A CI
# guard (`python -m nexus_platform.brain_builder --check`) fails the build if the
# committed brain no longer matches its source docs, so a stale brain can't slip
# through. If you change a company's docs/db, rebuild + commit its brain.
# Keep the local ChromaDB caches below ignored (transient, not per-company brains).
